@startuml seq-church-account
title Church Account Lifecycle Flow

actor "Church Rep" as Church
actor "Admin" as Admin
participant "AdminController" as API
participant "ChurchAccountService" as Service
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

Church -> API: POST /churches/apply\n{name, contactEmail, logoUrl}
API -> Service: createApplication(data)
Service -> DB: insert ChurchAccount\n(status: APPLIED)
DB --> Service: created
Service --> API: applicationId
API --> Church: application submitted

Admin -> API: GET /admin/churches?status=APPLIED
API -> DB: query pending applications
DB --> API: applications list
API --> Admin: church applications

Admin -> API: POST /admin/churches/{id}/review
API -> Service: beginReview(churchId)
Service -> DB: update status = PENDING_APPROVAL
API --> Admin: under review

Admin -> API: POST /admin/churches/{id}/approve\n{features: ["playlists", "branding"]}
API -> Service: approve(churchId, features)
Service -> DB: update status = ACTIVE\nset approvedAt, features[]
DB --> Service: approved
Service --> API: church activated
API --> Admin: approved

note over Church
  Church can now:
  - Set custom branding (logo, colors)
  - Curate playlists for congregation
  - View engagement for their playlists
end note

@enduml
